    Benchmarking ‘collections’

    benchmark.Rmd

    The goal of this document is to compare the performances of some of the existing packages. See benchmark.Rmd for the details.

    We are comparing these packages with collections.

    • dequer 2.0-1
    • datastructures 0.2.8
    • liqueueR 0.0.1
    • hash 2.2.6.1
    • hashmap 0.2.2
    • base: R native methods implemented by collections

    Queue

    microbenchmark(
    dequer = test_dequer_queue_push_pop(100),
    datastructures = test_datastructures_queue_push_pop(100),
    liqueueR = test_liqueueR_queue_push_pop(100),
    base = test_collections_queue_l_push_pop(100),
    collections = test_collections_queue_push_pop(100),
    unit = "relative"
)
    ## Unit: relative
##            expr   min    lq   mean median    uq    max neval
##          dequer  1.00  1.00  1.000   1.00  1.00  1.000   100
##  datastructures  8.42  8.26 23.749   8.43  8.34 56.947   100
##        liqueueR 13.94 13.57 10.098  13.68 13.10  3.948   100
##            base  2.71  2.74  2.059   2.80  2.78  0.372   100
##     collections  1.13  1.15  0.835   1.17  1.19  0.259   100
    microbenchmark(
    dequer = test_dequer_queue_push_pop(1000),
    base = test_collections_queue_l_push_pop(1000),
    collections = test_collections_queue_push_pop(1000),
    unit = "relative"
)
    ## Unit: relative
##         expr  min   lq mean median   uq  max neval
##       dequer 1.84 1.85 1.74   1.84 1.78 1.62   100
##         base 4.76 4.80 4.90   4.89 5.84 5.44   100
##  collections 1.00 1.00 1.00   1.00 1.00 1.00   100
